@page "/step03"

<div class="m-4">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900">Step 03 - Add Tailwind styling</h1>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-8 text-3xl">
        <li>Visit the <a class="text-sky-500 hover:text-sky-600" href="https://play.tailwindcss.com/">https://play.tailwindcss.com/</a> to play with tailwind and see changes in realtime with code completion</li>
        <li>
            Understand shorthand syntax for basic styling:
            <ul class="list-disc ml-8 text-3xl">
                <li>padding<pre>p-2 px-4 py-8 pb-1 pt-2 pl-3 pr-4 </pre></li>
                <li>margin<pre>m-2 mx-4 my-8 mb-1 mt-2 ml-3 mr-4 </pre></li>
                <li>
                    font size<pre>text-xs text-sm text-base text-lg text-xl </pre>
                    <p class="text-base ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-lg ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-xl ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-2xl ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    text color<pre>text-black text-white text-red-500 text-blue-600/40</pre>
                    <p class="text-black ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-red-500 ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-blue-200 ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-blue-600 ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                    <p class="text-blue-600/40 ...">The quick brown fox ...</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Also read this as a comparision between traditional and tailwind approach: <a class="text-sky-500 hover:text-sky-600" href="https://tailwindcss.com/docs/utility-first"s>https://tailwindcss.com/docs/utility-first</a></li>
        <li>
            To re-use styling parts like this:
            <pre>&lt;button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded"&gt;</pre>
            <div class="m-4">
                <button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">
                    Button1
                </button>
                <button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">
                    Button2
                </button>
            </div>
            We can create reusable Blazor components, see next item. Check the generated minified css to see used classes are added automatically by the tailwind exe. (may take a sec).
        </li>
        <li>Go to next page: <a href="/step04">Next</a></li>
    </ul>
</div>
